. “Over the last three years we have seen the Summer Cup grow phenomenally. The introduction of the half-time show and the carnival, and all the carnival elements, made a huge impact and so this year we’ve created a VIP version of the Summer Garden to accommodate the increasing interest in the area.”Guests can expect a fun line-up of DJs, a beautifully styled area, complete with flower walls for those perfect photo ops, an impressive crowd of sartorially minded visitors and great food and drinks. A partnership with Valdo, the leading producer of fine Prosecco, has been confirmed so expect a few elegant surprises and loads of delicious Rose and bubbles.Of course, it’s all about the racing, and there’s no better spot from which to watch the action, than the trackside Summer Garden.“We look forward to hosting our Summer Garden guests this year, and to introducing a whole new group of people to the thrill of horseracing,” says Campbell.SUMMER GARDEN INFORMATIONSummer Garden tickets sell for R295 (general access) and R995 (VIP). Under 18s pay R20.Bookings: vaughnine@campbellandcapbell.co.zabRev('brev-f4ddd9c5-3276-452c-acae-80fc0eaeb213', '>a/\<az.oc.llebpacdnallebpmac@eninhguav>"az.oc.llebpacdnallebpmac;46#&eninhguav:otliam"=ferh "knalb_"=tegrat a<'), 082 415 5840or https://www.webtickets.co.za/v2/EventCategory.aspx?itemid=1492401994Information: facebook.com/CampbellandCampbellSAGAUTENG SUMMER CUP INFORMATIONDate: Saturday 30 November 2019Gates open at 11amVenue: Turffontein Racecourse, 14 Turf Club Street, JohannesburgCONTACTFor general event information and bookings:info@gautengsummercup.co.zabRev('brev-59e8f8c9-9266-4cbb-803b-3ba40aa268d0', '>a/\<az.oc.pucremmusgnetuag@ofni>"az.oc.pucremmusgnetuag;46#&ofni:otliam"=ferh "knalb_"=tegrat a<'), 073 202 8308www.gautengsummercup.co.zaFollow the Gauteng Summer Cup:Facebook: @gautengsummercupTwitter: @gpsummercupLinkedIn: @GautengSummerCup